  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Mitigating Forced Labour Risks and Promoting Responsible Recruitment within the Operations of Members of the Consumer Goods Forum &#x2013; Human Rights Coalition - Working to End Forced Labour (CGF-HRC) and Their Palm Supply Chain in Malaysia</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The International Organization for Migration (IOM) and the Fair Labor Association (FLA) will support the Consumer Goods Forum and its Human Rights Coalition members (CGF-HRC) in their efforts to combat forced labour in owned operations and supply chains, promote responsible recruitment and help the palm oil plantation sector in Malaysia to detect and address exploitative labour practices within the CGF-HRC member companies&#x2019; labour supply chain, and finally to create a plan for the CGF-HRC member on Human Rights Due Diligence (HDCC) advocacy.</narrative>
  </description>
